seo_description: A young woman is declared brain-dead after a serious accident, and her husband callously says, “If you’re going to die, just say so.” Betrayed by both her father and husband, she is reborn three months later—this time with all her memories intact. She signs divorce papers and sends them to her husband. Every injustice she suffered is reflected back on him. Vengeance evolves into love, and a new chapter begins.
